🧾 TO DO: Xtrata Public On-Chain Message Board (Bug Report Layer)

🎯 Objective

Create a public, on-chain message board where anyone can submit short messages (e.g. bug reports, feedback, notes) via a Stacks transaction, and have those messages rendered inside a permanent Xtrata inscription.

This should demonstrate:
	•	Xtrata as a deterministic UI execution layer
	•	Stacks contracts as transactional state storage
	•	Composable “inscription + contract” architecture
	•	A live, immutable public document that updates via blockchain state

⸻

🧱 High-Level Architecture

We are building two components:

1️⃣ Stacks Contract: xtrata-message-board.clar

Responsible for:
	•	Accepting user-submitted messages
	•	Storing messages in contract state
	•	Enforcing limits (length, anti-spam fee, rate limits)
	•	Exposing read-only pagination endpoints

This contract is the canonical data source.

⸻

2️⃣ Xtrata Inscription: Viewer / Renderer

A small HTML/JS inscription that:
	•	Calls contract read-only functions via Stacks RPC
	•	Fetches paginated messages
	•	Renders them as a public document
	•	Optionally includes a “Post Message” button that connects wallet

This inscription is the public face of the document.

It is immutable.
The contract state changes.
The rendering logic does not.

⸻

