📦 Contract Specification (V1)

Data Model
	•	Max message length: 256–512 chars
	•	Each message stores:
	•	id
	•	sender (principal)
	•	block-height
	•	message
	•	optional fee-paid

Use indexed storage pattern:
	•	(define-data-var message-count uint u0)
	•	(define-map messages uint { sender: principal, block: uint, text: (string-ascii 512) })

⸻

Public Functions

post-message (text (string-ascii 512))

Requirements:
	•	Reject if text length > max
	•	Enforce minimum STX fee (anti-spam)
	•	Optionally enforce 1 message per principal per X blocks

Behavior:
	•	Increment message-count
	•	Insert into map
	•	Return new ID

⸻

Read-Only Functions

get-count

Returns total message count.

get-message (id uint)

Returns a single message.

get-page (offset uint, limit uint)

Returns bounded list.

⚠️ IMPORTANT:
Never design a function that returns all messages.
Pagination from day one.

⸻

🖥 Viewer Inscription Specification

This will be inscribed via Xtrata as a small HTML/JS file.

It should:
	1.	Display title:

Xtrata Public Message Board


	2.	Load latest 20 messages by:
	•	Calling get-count
	•	Fetching last N messages via pagination
	3.	Render in simple format:

[#123]  SPXXXX...
Block 123456
Message text...


	4.	Include:
	•	“Load more” button
	•	Optional wallet connect + post form

⸻

🔗 Integration with Xtrata

Two possible implementations:

⸻

Option A (Simpler V1)

Messages stored directly in contract state only.

Viewer:
	•	Reads via Stacks RPC
	•	No separate message inscriptions

Best for:
	•	Fast deployment
	•	Clean proof-of-concept

⸻

Option B (More Xtrata-native, scalable)

Contract stores:
	•	message ID
	•	hash of message
	•	pointer to Xtrata inscription ID

Message body:
	•	Inscribed separately via Xtrata

Viewer:
	•	Fetches pointer from contract
	•	Loads inscription via Xtrata
	•	Verifies hash

Best for:
	•	Large scale
	•	Keeps contract state small
	•	Demonstrates recursive composability

⸻

🛡 Anti-Spam & Moderation Strategy

Must include at least one of:
	•	Minimum STX posting fee
	•	Block-based rate limiting per principal
	•	Optional curator role for “pinning”

No censorship at contract level.
UI-level filtering permitted.

⸻

🧮 Cost Considerations
	•	256–512 char strings are acceptable in Clarity
	•	Must account for:
	•	Contract storage growth
	•	Read-only payload limits
	•	Gas cost per write

Posting must always require a transaction.
No off-chain writes.

